  <body>
    <header>
      <para styleclass="Heading1">Dialog: Plane</para>
    </header>
    <para styleclass="Heading2" style="page-break-before:always;">Add / Edit Plane</para>
    <para styleclass="SeeAlso">See also: <link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MD-Model-elements(Model)-AddPlane">Model Editor &gt; Add Plane</link> and <link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MD-Command-ModelElements(Mechanism)-AddPlane">Mechanism-Editor &gt; Add Plane</link></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><line style="height:1px; color:#993300;" /></para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo">You add <text styleclass="Interface">Mechanism-Editors</text> to <text styleclass="Element">Planes</text>. </para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo">When you do <text styleclass="T_Menu">Add Plane</text><text styleclass="Body Text">, the </text><text styleclass="Element">Plane dialog-box</text> opens to specify its parameter(s) immediately.</para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo">At any time also, you can open the <text styleclass="Element">Plane dialog-box</text><text styleclass="Body Text"> to edit the parameters of any </text><text styleclass="Element">Plane</text><text styleclass="Body Text"> that you have added to the model</text><text styleclass="Element">.</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><line style="height:1px; color:#993300;" /></para>
    <para styleclass="Heading4 Toggle_atocs_">Open Plane dialog-box</para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><table styleclass="Standard" rowcount="1" colcount="2" style="width:auto; head-row-background-color:#ffffff; alt-row-background-color:none;">
      <thead style="vertical-align:top">
        <td style="width:240px; border-right:none;">
          <para styleclass="Interface" style="text-align:right;"><image src="MD-AT-EditPlane.png" scale="-99.90%" styleclass="Image Caption" figurelistinclude="0"><caption><![CDATA[Edit Plane]]></caption></image></para>
        </td>
        <td style="border-left:none;">
          <para styleclass="Body Table">The <text styleclass="Element">Plane dialog box</text> opens when you do <text styleclass="T_Menu">Add Plane</text>.</para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo">To edit a <text styleclass="Element">Plane</text> that you have added to the model:</para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><table styleclass="PopupTable2" rowcount="1" colcount="1">
            <tr style="vertical-align:top">
              <td style="border-top:none; border-right:none; border-bottom:none;">
                <list id="0" type="ol" listtype="decimal" formatstring="&#37;&#48;&#58;&#115;&#46;" format-charset="DEFAULT_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="B Bullets" style="font-family:&apos;Segoe UI Semibold&apos;; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; color:#000000;">
                  <li styleclass="B Bullets"><text styleclass="Body Text Howindent4bullets">Right-click a </text><text styleclass="Element">Plane</text><text styleclass="Body Text Howindent4bullets"> in the </text><text styleclass="Interface">Assembly-Tree</text><text styleclass="VariableName">. </text></li>
                  <li styleclass="B Bullets"><text styleclass="Body Text">Click </text><text styleclass="VariableName">Edit-element</text><text styleclass="Body Text"> in the contextual-menu</text></li>
                </list>
                <para styleclass="VariableName-IT">- or -</para>
                <list id="1" type="ol" listtype="decimal" formatstring="&#37;&#48;&#58;&#115;&#46;" format-charset="DEFAULT_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="B Bullets" style="font-family:&apos;Segoe UI Semibold&apos;; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; color:#000000;">
                  <li styleclass="B Bullets"><text styleclass="SeeAlso">See </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MD-Dialog-How-to-Open-a-Dialog-Box" styleclass="SeeAlso">How to Open a Dialog-Box</link><text styleclass="VariableName">&#32;</text></li>
                </list>
              </td>
            </tr>
          </table></para>
          <para styleclass="Body Table">The <text styleclass="Element">Plane dialog-box</text> is now open.</para>
        </td>
      </thead>
    </table></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><line style="height:1px; color:#993300;" /></para>
    <para styleclass="Heading3_atocs_">Plane dialog-box</para>
    <para styleclass="Heading4 Toggle_atocs_" style="text-indent:-36px; margin-left:36px;"><text styleclass="Heading4 Toggle_atocs_2">&#32;</text><text styleclass="Body Text">The </text><text styleclass="Element">Plane dialog-box</text><text styleclass="Body Text"> has two configurations - which we call the </text><text styleclass="Parameter-Header">Plane Definitions</text><text styleclass="Body Text">.</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Heading4 Toggle_atocs_" style="text-indent:-36px; margin-left:36px;"><anchor id="PLANE-OFFSET" styleclass="Heading4 Toggle_atocs_2"><keywords><keyword>Plane Definition:<keyword>Offset from Plane</keyword></keyword></keywords></anchor><image src="tog_plus.gif" scale="100.00%" figurelistinclude="0"></image><tab /><toggle type="dropdown" print-expanded="true" help-expanded="false" defaultstyle="false" src-collapsed="tog_plus.gif" src-expanded="tog_minus.gif"><caption><![CDATA[Plane Definition 1: Offset from Plane]]></caption></toggle></para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><table styleclass="Default" rowcount="1" colcount="2">
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td style="vertical-align:bottom; width:240px;">
          <para styleclass=" " style="text-align:left; text-indent:0px; margin-top:0px; margin-right:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; line-height:1.00; background-color:transparent; white-space:normal; page-break-inside:auto; page-break-after:auto; border:none; tabstops:none;"><image src="MD-Dialog-AddPlane-Offset.png" scale="-99.90%" style="font-family:&apos;Segoe UI&apos;; font-size:8pt; font-weight:normal; font-style:normal; text-decoration:none; text-transform:none; vertical-align:baseline; color:#000000; background-color:transparent; letter-spacing:normal; letter-scaling:100%;" figurelistinclude="0"></image></para>
        </td>
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Body Table"><image src="Red-14-1b.gif" scale="100.00%" styleclass="Image Caption" figurelistinclude="0"></image>&#32;<text styleclass="VariableName">New Plane</text><text styleclass="Interface">:</text><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo">&#32;</text><text styleclass="Parameter">Plane6</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Body Table"><image src="Red-14-2.gif" scale="100.00%" styleclass="Image Caption" figurelistinclude="0"></image>&#32;<text styleclass="VariableName">Plane Definition</text><text styleclass="Parameter">: Offset from Plane</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Body Table"><image src="Red-14-4.gif" scale="100.00%" styleclass="Image Caption" figurelistinclude="0"></image>&#32;<text styleclass="VariableName">Element</text>&#32;<text styleclass="VariableName">box</text>- the element you select as the reference for the <text styleclass="VariableName">Plane Definition</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Body Table">&#32;<text styleclass="VariableName">Parameter to edit</text>:</para>
          <para styleclass="Body Table">&#32;<image src="Red-14-3.gif" scale="100.00%" styleclass="Image Caption" figurelistinclude="0"></image><text styleclass="Image Caption">&#32;</text><text styleclass="Parameter-Header">Distance to New Plane</text><text style="font-style:italic;">&#32;</text><text styleclass="HowTo Bulleted">&#32;</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Body Table">The offset dimension from the <text styleclass="Element">Plane</text> in the <text styleclass="Interface">Element</text> box<image src="Red-14-4.gif" scale="100.00%" styleclass="Image Caption" figurelistinclude="0"></image> to the new <text styleclass="Element">Plane</text><image src="Red-14-1b.gif" scale="100.00%" styleclass="Image Caption" figurelistinclude="0"></image>&#32;</para>
          <para styleclass="Normal"><line style="height:1px; color:#993300;" /></para>
          <para styleclass="Notes">Notes:</para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo">The XY-axis that define the new <text styleclass="Element">Plane</text> is: </para>
          <list id="2" type="ul" listtype="bullet" formatstring="&#183;" format-charset="SYMBOL_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="HowTo Bulleted" style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; color:#000000;">
            <li styleclass="HowTo Bulleted">parallel to the selected <text styleclass="Element">Plane</text><text styleclass="Body Text">&#32;</text></li>
            <li styleclass="HowTo Bulleted">on the <text styleclass="Interface">Z-axis</text> of the selected <text styleclass="Element">Plane</text><text styleclass="Body Text"> at the </text><text styleclass="Parameter">Distance to new Plane</text></li>
          </list>
        </td>
      </tr>
    </table></para>
    <para styleclass="Heading4 Toggle_atocs_" style="text-indent:-36px; margin-left:36px;"><anchor id="PLANE-ANGLE"><keywords><keyword>Plane Definition:<keyword>Angle from Line</keyword></keyword></keywords></anchor><image src="tog_plus.gif" scale="100.00%" figurelistinclude="0"></image><tab /><toggle type="dropdown" print-expanded="true" help-expanded="false" defaultstyle="false" src-collapsed="tog_plus.gif" src-expanded="tog_minus.gif"><caption><![CDATA[Plane Definition 2: Angle from Line]]></caption></toggle></para>
